<Title><?start-line?>A
<?new-line?>Bill

<?new-line?>To
</Title>
<Number /><LongTitle><?start-line?><Para>
<Text>Amend the Equality Act 2010 to improve access to public buildings; and to <?new-line?>introduce six and twelve inch rules for step free access.<DateOfEnactment><DateText /></DateOfEnactment>
</Text>
</Para>
</LongTitle>
<DateOfEnactment><DateText /></DateOfEnactment>
<PrimaryPreamble>
<EnactingText>
<Para>
<Text>B<SmallCaps>e it enacted</SmallCaps> by the Queen’s most Excellent Majesty, by and with the advice and <?new-line?>consent of the Lords Spiritual and Temporal, and Commons, in this present <?new-line?>Parliament assembled, and by the authority of the same, as follows:—</Text>
</Para>
</EnactingText>
</PrimaryPreamble>
</PrimaryPrelims>
<Body NumberFormat="default">
<P1group id="p00003">
<Title><?start-line?>Amendment to the Equality Act 2010</Title>
<P1>
<Pnumber>1</Pnumber>
<P1para>
<P2 id="p00004">
<Pnumber>1</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>The Equality Act 2010 is amended as follows.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
<P2>
<Pnumber>2</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>After subsection (9) insert the following new subsection—</Text>
<BlockAmendment TargetClass="primary" Context="main" TargetSubClass="unknown" Format="double">
<P2 id="p00005">
<Pnumber>9A</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>Reasonable steps taken under subsection (4) shall require buildings to <?new-line?>introduce a ramp, suitable for wheelchair access, in substitution for a <?new-line?>single access step if the single access step is of less than six inches.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
</BlockAmendment>
</P2para>
</P2>
<P2 id="p00006">
<Pnumber>3</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>After subsection (9) insert the following new subsection—</Text>
<BlockAmendment TargetClass="primary" Context="main" TargetSubClass="unknown" Format="double">
<P2 id="p00007">
<Pnumber>9B</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>Reasonable steps taken under subsection (4) shall require buildings to <?new-line?>introduce a ramp, suitable for wheelchair access, in substitution for a <?new-line?>single access step if the single access step is of less than twelve inches.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
</BlockAmendment>
</P2para>
</P2>
<P2 id="p00008">
<Pnumber>4</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>After subsection (9) insert the following new subsection—</Text>
<BlockAmendment TargetClass="primary" Context="main" TargetSubClass="unknown" Format="double">
<P2>
<Pnumber>9C</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>Reasonable steps which require a building to introduce a ramp, as <?new-line?>referred to in subsection <InternalLink id="i00001" Ref="p00005">(9A)</InternalLink> and <InternalLink id="i00002" Ref="p00007">(9B)</InternalLink>, do not apply to buildings which <?new-line?>have more than one step in order to gain access.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
</BlockAmendment>
</P2para>
</P2>
</P1para>
</P1>
</P1group>
<P1group id="p00009">
<Title><?start-line?>Short title and commencement</Title>
<P1>
<Pnumber>2</Pnumber>
<P1para>
<P2>
<Pnumber>1</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>This Act may be cited as the Equality (Amendment) Act 2013.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
<P2>
<Pnumber>2</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>This Act comes into force on the day on which it is passed, save for the <?new-line?>provisions in subsections <InternalLink id="i00003" Ref="p00010">(3)</InternalLink> and <InternalLink id="i00004" Ref="p00011">(4)</InternalLink>.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
<P2 id="p00010">
<Pnumber>3</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>Section 1<InternalLink id="i00005" Ref="p00004">(1)</InternalLink> and <InternalLink id="i00006" Ref="p00008">(4)</InternalLink> come into force at the end of the period of twelve months <?new-line?>beginning with the day on which this Act is passed.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
<?new-page?><P2 id="p00011">
<Pnumber>4</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>Section 1<InternalLink id="i00007" Ref="p00006">(3)</InternalLink> comes into force at the end of the period of two years beginning <?new-line?>with the day on which this Act is passed.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
</P1para>
</P1>
</P1group>
